{{Infobox publisher | name = Philosopher's Information Center | image = Logo_for_Philosopher's_Information_Center.jpg | caption = | parent = | status = | traded_as = | predecessor = | founded = 1966 | founder = [[Richard H. Lineback]], Ph.D., | successor = | country = | headquarters = [[Bowling Green, Ohio]] | distribution = | keypeople = | publications = | topics = | genre = | imprints = | revenue = | owner = | numemployees = | url = {{URL|http://www.philinfo.org}} }}
The '''Philosopher's Information Center'''<ref>http://www.philinfo.org/</ref> is a nonprofit, educational organization dedicated to serving the global [[philosophy|philosophical]] community. The center was founded in 1967<ref>http://philindex.org/about/history/</ref> by [[Richard H. Lineback]], Ph.D.,<ref>http://philindex.org/about/history/</ref> who continues to serve as president.
The center is publisher and owner of ''The Philosopher's Index''.<ref>Lineback, Richard. H., ed. The Philosopher’s Index.1-47 vols. Philosopher’s Information Center: Bowling Green, Ohio, 1967-2015. Library of Congress, http://lccn.loc.gov/74250928</ref> ''The Philosopher's Index'' is a comprehensive bibliography of publications in philosophy and related disciplines that date back to 1902 and originate in 140 countries. Since its founding, the center has worked to expand the scope of ''The Philosopher's Index''. The center has received major funding from the [[National Endowment for the Humanities]] for retrospective, international and book projects.
